name				rotateimage
version				0.2-1
architecture			x86_gcc2

summary			"Rotate images"
Description			"A small applet to rotate an image and save the resulting image, using ImageMagick. Transparency is attempted, but will depend on the input file type.

The non-interactive script will grab the default saved from the GUI version. If this does not exist, it defaults to 45 degrees rotation.

Planned to be part of a larger graphics workflow application, but can be used standalone.

Menu position: Applications | Graphics
"

packager			"Michel Clasquin-Johnson <clasqm@mail.com>"
